## Results — Expert-Refined Excel (v2)

### Overall Score: 76.6%

| Group | Accuracy | Coverage | Stage 1 acc |
|---|---|---|---|
| Demographics | 97.2% | 100% | 96.0% |
| Histology | 36.8% | 71.7% | 98.0% |
| Endoscopy | 80.0% | 15.6% | 0% |
| Baseline CT | 100% | 3.0% | 0% |
| Baseline MRI | 100% | 11.3% | 0% |
| 1st MDT | 94.7% | 76.0% | 48% |

**Category 1 — Demographics (×0.4):** 97.2%  
**Category 2 — Clinical (×0.6):** 62.9%  
**★ Overall: 76.6%**

### Error Attribution

- Stage 1 errors: 148 (78% of all failures)
- Stage 2 errors: 42 (22% of all failures)

### Key Findings

**Histology (36.8% accuracy):** Stage 2 is placing the differentiation grade ("Moderately differentiated") into the diagnosis column — 22 cases. The correct diagnosis is present in the JSON but Stage 2 maps the wrong sub-field. This is a pure Stage 2 bug fixable with one line in the deterministic map.

**CT / MRI (100% accuracy, low coverage):** When imaging values are extracted they are always correct. The coverage problem (3% and 11.3%) traces to Stage 1 — CT and MRI data were not separated into dedicated JSON fields, so Stage 2 had no structured data to map from.

**1st MDT (94.7% accuracy):** One genuine hallucination (case_03: "downstaging nCRT" when source says "watch and wait"). All other values are correct under permissive matching.

**80% of all errors originate at Stage 1.** The primary fix is the updated Stage 1 prompt (v2) which introduces dedicated structured fields for CT, MRI, and endoscopy data rather than a single unstructured blob.

